<span id="fn_378"></span>[75:3](sbe0529.htm#fr_381.md) The sacred formula
most frequently recited by the Parsis, and often several times in
succession, like the Pater-noster of some Christians; it is not,
however, a prayer, but a declaratory formula in 'praise of
righteousness' (which phrase is often used as its name in Pahlavi). It
consists of twelve Avesta words, as follows:

Ashem vohû vahi*s*tem astî,  
u*s*tâ astî; u*s*tâ ahmâi  
hya*d* ashâi vahi*s*tâi ashem.

<span class="contnote">\[paragraph continues\]</span> And it may be
translated in the following manner: 'Righteousness is the best good, a
