16), and the Bundahi*s* probably means to trace its course down the Âmû
(Oxus) from Sogdiana, across the Caspian, up the Aras (Araxes) or the
Kur (Cyrus), through the Euxine and Mediterranean, and up the Nile to
the Indian Ocean. The Âmû (Oxus) is also sometimes considered a part of
